    <title>
      <narrative xml:lang="en">Strengthening the Public Health System in the U.S. - Affiliated Pacific Islands (non-PPHF)</narrative>
    </title>
    <description type="1">
      <narrative xml:lang="en">Strengthening U.S. - Affiliated Pacific Islands (USAPI) Health Systems through Effective Leadership and Improved Capacities and Capabilities. The purpose of this funding initiative to ensure provision of capacity building assistance (CBA) to the USAPIs public health officials and public health systems. Capacity building efforts will support the formation of sound policies, strengthened organizational structures (e.g., governance, workforce recruitment/retention, and health services), effective management and revenue control, build jurisdictional partnerships, and address important cross-cutting issues such as health equity programs and services, and improved accountability measures for performance effectiveness and efficiency.</narrative>
    </description>
